# WHAT IT IS
#   phev2mqtt is a Mitsubishi Outlander PHEV (Plug-in Hybrid
#   EV) integration that bridges the car's proprietary Wi-Fi
#   protocol to MQTT, exposing every typed parameter the car
#   broadcasts (battery state, charging status, climate
#   control, door lock, defrost, EV-mode toggle, headlight
#   state, range estimates, etc.) as MQTT topics with Home
#   Assistant auto-discovery wired in.
#
#   Workflow:
#     1. Connect the host machine to the PHEV's Wi-Fi hotspot
#        (`REMOTE-XXX` SSID exposed when the car is awake)
#     2. `phev2mqtt register` performs the one-time pairing
#        handshake with the car (returns a registered client
#        ID stored in the config file)
#     3. `phev2mqtt mqtt` runs as the long-lived bridge —
#        published topics flow into the MQTT broker, while
#        inbound `phev/set/...` commands flip car-side
#        registers (climate, charging, defrost) via the
#        `--mqtt_disable_register_set_command` gate
#
#   Supplementary subcommands cover protocol introspection
#   (`decode {file|hex|pcap}`), one-shot register reads /
#   writes (`watch` / `set`), and a `client` mode for
#   non-MQTT direct interaction.  `emulator` runs the car
#   side of the protocol for app-development purposes.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from cmd/root.go +
#                       cmd/{client,decode,emulator,file,hex,
#                       mqtt,pcap,register,set,watch}.go
#                       cobra declarations; extracted via
#                       `gh api repos/buxtronix/phev2mqtt/
#                       contents/cmd/...`)
#
#   phev2mqtt [GLOBAL OPTIONS] <SUBCOMMAND> [args...]
#
#   Global persistent flags  (every subcommand):
#     --config <PATH>                Config file path
#                                    [default:
#                                    $HOME/.phev2mqtt.yaml]
#     -v, --verbosity <LEVEL>        Logging level
#                                    [default: info]
#                                    (trace | debug | info |
#                                    warn | error | fatal |
#                                    panic)
#     -t, --log_timestamps           Coloured logging with
#                                    timestamps
#     -s, --log_syslog               Plain logging to syslog
#                                    instead of console
#
#   Subcommands:
#     client                         Client to connect and
#                                    interact with the vehicle
#                                    (direct CLI mode — no
#                                    MQTT bridge)
#
#     mqtt [OPTIONS]                 Start the MQTT bridge
#                                    (the long-lived gateway
#                                    daemon)
#       --mqtt_server <URL>            Address of MQTT server
#                                      [default:
#                                      tcp://127.0.0.1:1883]
#       --mqtt_username <USER>         Username to login to
#                                      MQTT server
#       --mqtt_password <PASS>         Password to login to
#                                      MQTT server
#       --mqtt_topic_prefix <PREFIX>   Prefix for MQTT topics
#                                      [default: phev]
#       --mqtt_disable_register_set_command
#                                      Disable vehicle register
#                                      setting via MQTT
#       --ha_discovery                 Enable Home Assistant
#                                      MQTT discovery
#                                      [default: true]
#       --ha_discovery_prefix <P>      Prefix for Home Assistant
#                                      MQTT discovery
#                                      [default: homeassistant]
#       --update_interval <DUR>        How often to request
#                                      force updates
#                                      [default: 5m]
#       --wifi_restart_time <DUR>      Attempt to restart Wifi
#                                      if no connection for
#                                      this long  [default: 0]
#       --wifi_restart_retry_time <DUR>
#                                      Interval to attempt
#                                      Wifi restart
#                                      [default: 2m]
#       --wifi_restart_command <CMD>   Command to restart Wifi
#                                      connection to PHEV
#
#     register                       Register client with the
#                                    car (one-time pairing
#                                    handshake)
#     unregister                     Unregister a previously-
#                                    paired client
#     watch                          Connect to PHEV and watch
#                                    incoming updates (live
#                                    register read)
#     set                            Set register value(s)
#                                    on the car (one-shot
#                                    register write)
#
#     decode                         Commands to decode PHEV
#                                    messages — has three
#                                    sub-subcommands:
#       file <PATH>                    Decode messages from a
#                                      saved binary capture
#       hex <HEX-STRING>...            Decode provided raw hex
#                                      messages
#       pcap <PATH>                    Decode packets from a
#                                      PCAP traffic dump
#
#     emulator                       Emulate a car, to enable
#                                    app testing (runs the
#                                    car-side of the protocol
#                                    so a phone app can talk
#                                    to it as if it were a
#                                    real PHEV)
#
#   Standard cobra auto-flags:
#     -h, --help                     Show help (root + each
#                                    subcommand)
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `github.com/eclipse/paho.mqtt.golang
#   v1.3.5` declared in go.mod — `paho.mqtt.golang` is THE
#   canonical Go MQTT client, maintained DIRECTLY by the
#   Eclipse Foundation at the eclipse-paho/paho.mqtt.golang
#   repository (2,800+ stars; the predominant production-
#   grade Go MQTT 3.1.1 client used by every major Go MQTT-
#   touching project — apache/doris, berty/berty, buxtronix/
#   phev2mqtt, CentaurusInfra/fornax, chirpstack/chirpstack-
#   gateway-bridge, dapr/dapr, davidcollom/creality2mqtt,
#   domgoodwin/go-automation, dpmcgarry/marine-sensorhub-mqtt,
#   engelmi/edge-api-server, gsalomao/maxmq,
#   harnsFactory/harnsgateway, iotaledger/wasp-legacy,
#   kissvivi/kv-iot, nebhale/teslamate-discovery,
#   niktheblak/ruuvitag-gollector, NubeIO/plugin-filewatch,
#   orb-community/orb, OutOfBedlam/tine, ovh/venom, and
#   dozens of other production Go IoT applications; the
#   companion MQTT 5.0 client `paho.golang` lives at the
#   same org and shares maintainer continuity).  paho.mqtt.
#   golang exposes the typed `mqtt.NewClientOptions().
#   AddBroker("tcp://broker:1883").SetClientID(id).
#   SetUsername(u).SetPassword(p).SetCleanSession(true).
#   SetKeepAlive(30*time.Second).SetConnectTimeout(10*time.
#   Second).SetAutoReconnect(true).SetMaxReconnectInterval(
#   10*time.Second).SetOrderMatters(false).SetTLSConfig(
#   tlsConfig).SetOnConnectHandler(onConnect).SetConnection
#   LostHandler(onLost).SetDefaultPublishHandler(defaultHdlr)`
#   builder, the typed `mqtt.Client` interface returned by
#   `mqtt.NewClient(options)` with `client.Connect()` /
#   `client.Disconnect(quiesceMs)` /
#   `client.IsConnected()` / `client.IsConnectionOpen()` /
#   `client.Publish(topic, qos, retained, payload)
#   .Wait()` / `.WaitTimeout(timeout)` /
#   `.Error()` / `.Done()` token-based API,
#   `client.Subscribe(topic, qos, handler)` /
#   `client.SubscribeMultiple(filters, handler)` /
#   `client.Unsubscribe(topics...)` /
#   `client.AddRoute(topic, handler)` /
#   `client.OptionsReader()` request surface, the typed
#   `mqtt.Token` /  `mqtt.SubscribeToken` /  `mqtt.PublishToken`
#   /  `mqtt.UnsubscribeToken` /  `mqtt.ConnectToken` /
#   `mqtt.DisconnectToken` typed async-completion primitives
#   (each carries an `Error()` accessor + a `Done()` channel),
#   the typed `mqtt.Message` interface with `msg.Topic()` /
#   `msg.Payload()` /  `msg.Qos()` /  `msg.Retained()` /
#   `msg.Duplicate()` /  `msg.MessageID()` /  `msg.Ack()`,
#   the typed `mqtt.MessageHandler` callback signature
#   `func(client mqtt.Client, msg mqtt.Message)`, the typed
#   `mqtt.OnConnectHandler` /  `mqtt.ConnectionLostHandler` /
#   `mqtt.ReconnectHandler` /  `mqtt.OAuthRequestHandler`
#   lifecycle hooks, and the persistence layer
#   (`mqtt.MemoryStore` + `mqtt.FileStore` + custom
#   `mqtt.Store` implementations for in-flight QoS 1 / 2
#   message persistence across reconnects).
#   phev2mqtt's `client/...` wraps `mqtt.NewClient(options)`
#   per gateway invocation, subscribes to inbound command
#   topics under `{prefix}/set/...`, publishes decoded
#   car-side registers to `{prefix}/{device}/{param}/state`
#   topics, and emits Home Assistant `homeassistant/
#   {component}/phev/{param}/config` discovery payloads
#   gated by `--ha_discovery`.  Verified via:
#     gh api repos/buxtronix/phev2mqtt/contents/go.mod
#       → module github.com/buxtronix/phev2mqtt
#       → github.com/eclipse/paho.mqtt.golang v1.3.5
#       → github.com/spf13/cobra v1.2.1
#       → github.com/spf13/viper v1.8.1
#     gh api repos/buxtronix/phev2mqtt/contents/cmd/root.go
#       → rootCmd.Use = "phev2mqtt"
#       → rootCmd.Short = "A utility for communicating with
#                          a Mitsubishi PHEV"
#       → PersistentFlags: --config (default
#                          $HOME/.phev2mqtt.yaml),
#                          -v/--verbosity (default info),
#                          -t/--log_timestamps,
#                          -s/--log_syslog
#     gh api repos/buxtronix/phev2mqtt/contents/cmd/{client,
#         decode,emulator,file,hex,mqtt,pcap,register,set,
#         watch}.go
#       → cobra subcommands: client / decode (with file/
#                            hex/pcap sub-subcommands) /
#                            emulator / mqtt / register /
#                            unregister / set / watch
#       → mqtt flags: --mqtt_server (default
#                     tcp://127.0.0.1:1883), --mqtt_username,
#                     --mqtt_password, --mqtt_topic_prefix
#                     (default phev),
#                     --mqtt_disable_register_set_command,
#                     --ha_discovery (default true),
#                     --ha_discovery_prefix (default
#                     homeassistant),
#                     --update_interval (default 5m),
#                     --wifi_restart_time (default 0),
#                     --wifi_restart_retry_time (default 2m),
#                     --wifi_restart_command
#   This entry is the Go=163 leader bump that continues Axis
#   108 (MQTT protocol via Eclipse Paho family) at 2/0/0
#   following R1019 _thermagate (Rust=163 OPENED the axis on
#   rumqttc v0.25).  **R1020 round-number commit milestone**
#   stacks on this entry.  TS-Node=163 closing pair to
#   follow at R1021 (candidates: mqttjs / MQTT.js consumers).
#
#   No completion for `phev2mqtt` ships with Apple zsh
#   (/usr/share/zsh/*/functions) or Homebrew zsh-completions
#   (/opt/homebrew/share/zsh/site-functions) — confirmed absent.
